These are some basic Linux commands I learned during my cybersecurity training.
--> Basic Commands
pwd = shows the current directory
ls = Lists all files and folders
cd <folder_name> = Used to move to another directory.
mkdir <folder_name> = Creates a new folder.
rmdir <folder_name> = Removes an empty folder.
touch <file_name> = Creates a new file.
cp <source> <destination> = Copies a file or folder.
mv <source> <destination> = Moves or renames a file.
rm <file_name> = Deletes a file.
cat <file_name> = Displays the content of a file.

--> User & Network Commands
whoami = Shows the current user.
hostname = Displays the system name.
groups = Shows the groups of the current user.
ifconfig = Displays network information.
ip route = Shows the routing table.
